title: 'Wonderful visit to Australia': Netanyahu - 9news.com.au
text:
'Wonderful visit to Australia': Netanyahu By AAP 
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says his inaugural tour to Australia has been "wonderful". 
The Israeli PM and his wife wind up their five-day trip to Sydney on Sunday, but he met with Foreign Minister Julie Bishop just hours before departing. 
"This has been a wonderful visit here. You people are amazing," Mr Netanyahu told the foreign minister before holding bilateral talks behind closed doors. 
The Israeli PM joked with Ms Bishop, who's just arrived home from a whirlwind trip to the US and UK, that the pair had "shared more or less the same route". 
Ms Bishop held high-level talks with top Trump administration officials in Washington including Lieutenant-General H R McMaster the newly appointed as the president's National Security Advisor. 
She also met Vice-President Mike Pence and Secretary of State Rex Tillerson, while in London she met with UK's Foreign Secretary Boris Johnson to discuss Brexit then onto Dublin in Ireland for trade talks with ministers. 
Mr Netanyahu flew into Sydney on Wednesday as the first sitting Israeli prime minister to touch down on Australian soil. 
On Sunday Mr Netanyahu praised the hospitality by Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull and his wife Lucy, and spoke of Sydney's "beautiful beaches". 
"I'd stay longer if I could," he said. 
Ms Bishop said the prime minister and his wife had been very happy to play host. 
"I know they were both very much looking forward to your visit."
